  "why": "The fuzzer explicitly uses mutation operators and LLM-assisted mutation to preserve semantic correctness at each mutation step (e.g., Rephrase, Shorten, Generate) and states these are designed to maintain semantic integrity. However, the paper does not present an explicit mechanism that measures or enforces cumulative distortion relative to the original seed across repeated mutation iterations (e.g., no similarity/perturbation budget or a generative model constrained to the plausible distribution). The only mechanism that indirectly limits deep mutation chains is a reward discount (α) tied to path depth in the MCTS-Explore seed selection, intended to improve exploration/diversity rather than to guarantee cumulative semantic plausibility. These facts match the metric definition for Medium: stepwise plausibility-preserving mutations but no explicit control of cumulative distortion across iterations.",
